The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Kanpur, June 10 (PTI): Authorities of several Kanpur colleges have barred students and teachers from wearing jeans, sleeveless blouses, danglers and high heels on campus.           
	College principals said the move was made to check eve-teasing and ensure discipline. While students would be reprimanded for flouting the rule, teachers would have to pay a fine of Rs 100.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The railways have decided to put curtains in the aisles of all air-conditioned three-tier coaches in order to give more privacy to passengers. Instructions have been sent to all the zonal railways and coach factories. Till now, curtains were provided only on the windows of AC three-tier coaches.                   
	 Nagpur (PTI): Bombay High Court on Wednesday pulled up the officials investigating the death of a seven-year-old girl whose body was found inside Maharashtra BJP president Nitin Gadkaris car. The court asked why the investigators did not record the statement of the cars owner on his first availability in the city. When you say the driver of the car locked the vehicle and kept the keys at the police guard room, how come the girl landed in the car? the court asked the investigators, observing that they did not follow the basic principles of investigation. Yogita was found dead in Gadkaris car on May 19.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The CBI on Wednesday conducted over 250 nation-wide searches on the offices of income tax, Doordarshan and CISF officials as part of its anti-corruption drive. Over Rs 1 crore in cash, gold biscuits, gold coins and various incriminating documents were seized.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Centre will declare 55 metres within important installations located along the 7,500km coastline as no-fishing zone in a bid to tighten maritime security. Three nuclear installations located at Kalpakkam and Kudankulam in Tamil Nadu and one in Mumbai have been notified as important installations and 500 metres around it will be declared as no-fishing zone.                                                                                                                           
